result.execSummary:
The defendant Breanna L Vandenbush was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Operate with Restricted Controlled Substance (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

REVOKED.  Sentenced to Jail/HOC.  Filed, sdg.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.
Court sentenced defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for 0 days served.  COURT IMPOSED BUT STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 2 years with the following conditions:

  - Cooperate with conditons set forth in Waukesha County Drug Treatment Court contract.
  - Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges by 09-01-2016 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.  Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.

Court will consider expungement upon successful completion of conditions of Waukesha County Drug Treatment Court contract.

Defendant Breanna L Vandenbush in court with attorney Daniel P Fay.  Brad A. Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing in Branch 6.  Review hearing scheduled for 01-05-2015 at 08:30 am.
Associated with Charge #2

AS TO COUNT 2 ONLY: 
Defendant changes her plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Statements by State, counsel and defendant as to sentencing.
Court sentenced defendant to serve 15 DAYS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence; Huber privileges for work and AODA treatment; credit for 0 days served.  Sentence to commence FORTHWITH.

Court sentenced defendant to pay a FINE of $350.00 PLUS all mandatory costs, penalties and surcharges to be paid by 10-03-2017.  Court orders penalty for nonpayment of fines is conversion to civil judgment and tax intercept.  

Court ordered AODA Assessment
Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for 12 months.
The Court orders an Ignition Interlock Device for 12 months beginning on the date the defendant is issued a driver's license.

Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.

Filed, signed Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  The court reviewed the Agreement with the defendant.  Corrections made. 
Pursuant to plea negotiations and AS TO COUNT 1 ONLY:  
The defendant was advised of her constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgment of Conviction as to Count 1 for a period of six months.  This six months commences upon the defendant's release from custody on Count 2.  The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and found it to be in the best interest of the parties and the general public.

Parties proceed to plea/sentencing of Count 2.  

Case adjourned to Branch 6.  Review hearing scheduled for December 1, 2014 at 08:30 am.
